PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanList.name: VlanList
VlanList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 1 through 8, the second octet specifying vlans 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan supported is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then the associated port is in that vlan; the port is not included if the vlans bit has a value of '0'.

agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThreshold.description: The CPU Rising utilization threshold in percentage. A zero percent threshold indicates CPU Utilization Notification feature is disabled. A notification is triggered when the total CPU utilization exceeds this threshold over the configured Rising threshold interval. If the Rising threshold is configured to be less than the Falling threshold, the Falling threshold is set equal to the Rising threshold.

agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInte.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInterval
agentSwitchCpuProcessRisingThresholdInte.description: The CPU Rising threshold interval in seconds. The time interval is configured in multiples of 5 seconds. A zero Rising interval indicates CPU Utilization Notification feature is disabled.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThreshold.description: The CPU Falling utilization threshold in percentage. Configuration of this object value is optional. Value '0' is not allowed for configuration, if the Rising threshold is non-zero. If the Falling threshold is configured to be greater than the Rising threshold, the Rising threshold is set equal to the Falling threshold. If the Falling threshold is not configured, it takes the same value as the Rising threshold. A notification is triggered when the total CPU utilization falls below this threshold over the configured Falling threshold interval.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInt.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInterval
agentSwitchCpuProcessFallingThresholdInt.description: The CPU Falling threshold interval in seconds. Configuration of this object value is optional. Value '0' is not allowed for configuration, if the Rising interval is non-zero. If the Falling interval is not configured, it takes the same value as the Rising interval. The time interval is configured in multiples of 5 seconds.

agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold.name: agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold
agentSwitchCpuProcessFreeMemoryThreshold.description: The CPU Free Memory threshold in kilobytes. A zero threshold value indicates the CPU Free Memory Notification feature is disabled. Notifications are triggered when the CPU Free Memory falls below the configured threshold and when it rises to 10% above the configured threshold.

agentTelnetLoginTimeout.description: Telnet login timeout (minutes) Config telnet timeout will set the telnet session timeout value. A session is active as long as the session has not remained idle for the value set. Specify a value from 1 to 160. Note: Changing the timeout value for active sessions does not become effective until the session is reaccessed. Any keystroke will also activate the new timeout duration.

agentTelnetMaxSessions.description: Maximum number of Telnet Sessions Config telnet maxsessions is an integer value from 0 to 5 that specifies the maximum number of telnet sessions that can be established. If the value is 0, no Telnet session can be established.

agentTelnetAllowNewMode.description: Allow new telnet sessions (enable or disable) Config telnet disable means that no new Telnet sessions are to be established. Any already established session remains active until the session is ended or an abnormal network error ends it.

agentLagSummaryPortStaticCapability.name: agentLagSummaryPortStaticCapability
agentLagSummaryPortStaticCapability.description: Agent LAG Static Capability enable(1) - Static capability is enabled for this LAG interface disable(2) - Static capability is disabled for this LAG interface

agentLagSummaryHash.name: agentLagSummaryHash
agentLagSummaryHash.description: Agent LAG HASH algorithm. Allow the user to specify which hash distribution algorithm want to be applied all LAG groups. src-mac(1) - Source MAC address. dst-mac(2) - Destination MAC address. src-dst-mac(3) - Source and Destination MAC address. src-ip(4) - Source IP address (IPv4 and IPv6). dst-ip(5) - Destination IP address (IPv4 and IPv6). src-dst-ip(6) - Source and Destination IP address (IPv4 and IPv6). src-ip-src-ipport(7) - Source IP address and Source IP L4 Port (IPv4 and IPv6). dst-ip-dst-ipport(8) - Destination IP address and Destination IP L4 Port (IPv4 and IPv6). src-dst-ip-ipports(9) - Source and Destination IP address and Source IP L4 Port and Destination IP L4 Port (IPv4 and IPv6)(default). src-dst-ip-x1(10) - Source and Destination IP address XOR Mode 1. src-dst-ip-x1(11) - Source and Destination IP address XOR Mode 2. src-dst-ip-x1(12) - Source and Destination IP address XOR Mode 4. src-dst-ip-x1(13) - Source and Destination IP address XOR Mode 8.

agentLagSummaryHashOption.name: agentLagSummaryHashOption

Valid values correspond to 1 (=Source MAC, VLAN, EtherType, and incoming port associated with the packet) 2 (=Destination MAC, VLAN, EtherType, and incoming port associated with the packet) 3 (=Source/Destination MAC, VLAN, EtherType, and incoming port associated with the packet) 4 (=Source IP and Source TCP/UDP fields of the packet) 5 (=Destination IP and Destination TCP/UDP Port fields of the packet) 6 (=Source/Destination IP and source/destination TCP/UDP Port fields of the packet) 7 (=Enhanced hashing mode) Support for particular options may vary by device.

agentLagConfigGroupHashOption.name: agentLagConfigGroupHashOption
agentLagConfigGroupHashOption.description: LAG Hashing Option. In BCM 53115 device only options 1 to 3 are support and only MAC address associated with the packet is used.

agentSnmpCommunityCreate.name: agentSnmpCommunityCreate
agentSnmpCommunityCreate.description: Creates a new SNMP Community entry. Defaults: IPAddress 0.0.0.0 IpMask 0.0.0.0 AccessMode read-only Status config

agentSnmpCommunityConfigTable.name: agentSnmpCommunityConfigTable
agentSnmpCommunityConfigTable.description: A table of the switch's SNMP Config entries

agentSnmpCommunityName.name: agentSnmpCommunityName
agentSnmpCommunityName.description: The switch's Snmp Community Name This name identifies each SNMP community; the name can be up to 16 characters, and it is case-sensitive. Community names in the SNMP community must be unique. If you make multiple entries using the same community name, the first entry is kept and processed and all duplicate entries are ignored.

agentSnmpCommunityIPAddress.name: agentSnmpCommunityIPAddress
agentSnmpCommunityIPAddress.description: The switch's Snmp Community IP Address Client IP Address - This attribute is an IP address (or portion thereof) from which this device will accept SNMP packets with the associated community. The requesting entity's IP address is logical-ANDed with the Client IP Mask and the result must match the Client IP Address. Note: If the Client IP Mask is set to 0.0.0.0, a Client IP Address of 0.0.0.0 matches all IP addresses.

agentSnmpCommunityIPMask.name: agentSnmpCommunityIPMask
agentSnmpCommunityIPMask.description: The switch's Snmp Community IP Mask Client IP Mask - This attribute is a mask to be logical-ANDed with the requesting entity's IP address before comparison with the Client IP Address. If the result matches with Client IP Address then the address is an authenticated IP address. For example, if the Client IP Address is 9.47.128.0 and the corresponding Client IP Mask is 255.255.255.0, a range of incoming IP addresses would match, that is, the incoming IP addresses could be a value in the following range: 9.47.128.0 to 9.47.128.255. To have a specific IP address be the only authenticated IP address, set the Client IP Address to the required IP address and set the Client IP Mask to 255.255.255.255.

agentSnmpCommunityAccessMode.name: agentSnmpCommunityAccessMode
agentSnmpCommunityAccessMode.description: The switch's Snmp Community Access Mode Access Mode - This value can be read-only or read/write. A community with a read-only access allows for switch information to be displayed. A community with a read/write access allows for configuration changes to be made and for information to be displayed.

agentSnmpCommunityStatus.name: agentSnmpCommunityStatus
agentSnmpCommunityStatus.description: The switch's Snmp Community Status. active(1) - This community is active, allowing SNMP managers associated with this community to manage the switch according to its access right. notInService(2) - This community is not active; no SNMP requests using this community will be accepted. In this case the SNMP manager associated with this community cannot manage the switch until the Status is changed back to active(1). config(3) - The community Status must be set to this value in order to configure it. When creating a new community entry, initial Status will be set to this value. destroy(4) - Set to this value to remove the community from the agent.

agentSnmpTrapReceiverCreate.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverCreate
agentSnmpTrapReceiverCreate.description: Creates a new trap receiver entry. Defaults: IPAddress 0.0.0.0 status config

agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigTable.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigTable
agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigTable.description: Trap messages are sent across a network to an SNMP Network Manager. These messages alert the manager to events occurring within the switch or on the network. Up to six simultaneous trap receivers are supported.

agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigEntry.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigEntry
agentSnmpTrapReceiverConfigEntry.description: Switch's Snmp Trace Receiver Config entry

agentSnmpTrapReceiverIndex.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverIndex
agentSnmpTrapReceiverIndex.description: The switch's Snmp Trap Receiver Index

agentSnmpTrapReceiverCommunityName.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverCommunityName
agentSnmpTrapReceiverCommunityName.description: The switch's Snmp Trap Receiver Community Name. This is the SNMP community name of the remote network manager; the name can be up to 16 characters, and is case-sensitive.

agentSnmpTrapReceiverIPAddress.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverIPAddress
agentSnmpTrapReceiverIPAddress.description: Trap receiver IP or IPv6 address

agentSnmpTrapReceiverStatus.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverStatus
agentSnmpTrapReceiverStatus.description: The switch's Snmp Trap Reciever Status. active(1) - This trap receiver is active, allowing SNMP Traps to be sent to this receiver. notInService(2) - This trap reciever is not active; no SNMP Traps will be sent to this reciever until it's set back to active(1). config(3) - The trap reciever Status must be set to this value in order to configure it. When creating a new trap receiver entry, the Status will initially be set to this value. Note: agentSnmpTrapReceiverIPAddress must be set to non-zero before changing to active(1) or notInService(2). destroy(4) - Set to this value to remove the trap receiver entry from the agent.

agentSnmpTrapReceiverVersion.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverVersion
agentSnmpTrapReceiverVersion.description: The version of trap sent to this Reciever. snmpv1(1) - This will send a SNMPv1 trap. snmpv2c(2) - This will send a SNMPv2c trap. snmpv3(3) - This will send a SNMPv3 trap.

agentSnmpTrapReceiverSecurityLevel.name: agentSnmpTrapReceiverSecurityLevel
agentSnmpTrapReceiverSecurityLevel.description: The security level of SNMPv3 trap reciever. none(1) - SNMPv3 noAuthNoPriv security level. auth(2) - SNMPv3 authNoPriv security level. priv(3) - SNMPv3 authPriv security level notSupport(4) - only support on SNMPv3

agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag
agentSnmpLinkUpDownTrapFlag.description: Link Up/Down Flag - Enable/Disable Link Up/Link Down traps for the entire switch. When set to Enable, the Link Up/Down traps will be sent only if the Link Trap flag setting associated with the port (Port Configuration Menu) is set to Enable.

agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag
agentSnmpMultipleUsersTrapFlag.description: Multiple Users Flag - Enable/Disable Multiple User traps. When the value is set to Enable, a Multiple User Trap is sent whenever someone logs in to the terminal interface (EIA 232 or Telnet) and there is already an existing terminal interface session.

agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag.name: agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag
agentSnmpSpanningTreeTrapFlag.description: Spanning Tree Flag - This flag enables the sending of new root traps and topology change notification traps.

agentSnmpInformAdminMode.name: agentSnmpInformAdminMode
agentSnmpInformAdminMode.description: The switch's Snmp Inform Admin Mode

agentSnmpInformConfigTableCreate.name: agentSnmpInformConfigTableCreate
agentSnmpInformConfigTableCreate.description: Creates a new trap inform entry. Defaults: IPAddress 0.0.0.0 status config

agentSnmpInformConfigTable.name: agentSnmpInformConfigTable
agentSnmpInformConfigTable.description: Trap messages are sent across a network to an SNMP Network Manager. These messages alert the manager to events occurring within the switch or on the network. Up to six simultaneous trap receivers are supported.

agentSnmpInformName.name: agentSnmpInformName
agentSnmpInformName.description: The switch's Snmp Inform Name. This is the SNMP community name of the remote network manager; the name can be up to 16 characters, and is case-sensitive.

agentSnmpInformIpAddress.name: agentSnmpInformIpAddress
agentSnmpInformIpAddress.description: The switch's Snmp Inform IP or IPv6 address.

agentSnmpInformVersion.name: agentSnmpInformVersion
agentSnmpInformVersion.description: The version of inform sent to this Reciever. snmpv2c(2) - This will send a SNMPv2c inform. snmpv3(3) - This will send a SNMPv3 inform.

agentSnmpInformStatus.name: agentSnmpInformStatus
agentSnmpInformStatus.description: The switch's Snmp Trap Inform Status. active(1) - This trap Inform is active, allowing SNMP Traps to be sent to this receiver. notInService(2) - This trap Inform is not active; no SNMP Traps will be sent to this reciever until it's set back to active(1). config(3) - The trap Inform Status must be set to this value in order to configure it. When creating a new trap receiver entry, the Status will initially be set to this value. Note: agentSnmpTrapReceiverIPAddress must be set to non-zero before changing to active(1) or notInService(2). destroy(4) - Set to this value to remove the trap Inform entry from the agent.

agentSnmpInformSecurityLevel.name: agentSnmpInformSecurityLevel
agentSnmpInformSecurityLevel.description: The security level of SNMPv3 trap inform. none(1) - SNMPv3 noAuthNoPriv security level. auth(2) - SNMPv3 authNoPriv security level. priv(3) - SNMPv3 authPriv security level notSupport(4) - only support on SNMPv3

agentSnmpUserAuthenticationPassword.name: agentSnmpUserAuthenticationPassword
agentSnmpUserAuthenticationPassword.description: The switch's Snmp User Authentication Password.

agentSnmpUserEncryptionPassword.name: agentSnmpUserEncryptionPassword
agentSnmpUserEncryptionPassword.description: The switch's Snmp User Encryption Password.

agentSnmpUserStatus.name: agentSnmpUserStatus
agentSnmpUserStatus.description: The status of SNMP user. active(1) - This snmp user is active. create(4) - Create a new SNMP user. destory(6) - Delete a SNMP user.

agentSnmpTrapSourceInterface.name: agentSnmpTrapSourceInterface
agentSnmpTrapSourceInterface.description: A source-interface selection on an Interface Index (like vlan based routing interface, port based routing interface, loopback interface, tunnel interface). A non-zero value indicates ifIndex for the corresponding interface entry in the ifTable is selected. A zero value indicates the source-interface un-selection.

agentSnmpEngineIdIpAddress.name: agentSnmpEngineIdIpAddress
agentSnmpEngineIdIpAddress.description: The switch's Snmp EngineID IP or IPv6 address.

agentSnmpEngineIdStatus.name: agentSnmpEngineIdStatus
agentSnmpEngineIdStatus.description: The status of SNMP EngineID. active(1) - This snmp EngineID is active. create(4) - Create a new SNMP EngineID. destory(6) - Delete a SNMP EngineID.

agentSpanningTreeMode.name: agentSpanningTreeMode
agentSpanningTreeMode.description: The switch's Spanning Tree Switch Status. This functionality is now handled by agentStpAdminMode

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutTable.description: The switch's address aging timeout table

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeoutEntry.description: Aging information about a specific Filtering Database.

agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout.name: agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout
agentSwitchAddressAgingTimeout.description: The FDB entry's address aging timeout (in seconds)

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringTable.description: The switch's static Mac filtering table

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringEntry.description: Per-port ingress/egress filter configuration based on VLAN Id and MAC address.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringVlanId.description: The Static MAC Filter Vlan Id

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringAddress.description: The Static MAC Filter MAC address

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortM.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortMask
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringSourcePortM.description: The Static MAC Filter source port mask. When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMas.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMask
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringDestPortMas.description: The Static MAC Filter destination port mask. When setting this value, the system will ignore configuration for ports not between the first and last valid ports. Configuration of any port numbers between this range that are not valid ports return a failure message, but will still apply configuration for valid ports. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table. Configuring destination port mask for a unicast MAC filter is not supported on some platforms.

agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus.name: agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus
agentSwitchStaticMacFilteringStatus.description: The Static MAC Filter status. Supported values: active(1) - valid entry createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry destroy(6) - removes the entry

agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable
agentSwitchSnoopingCfgTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Global configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingCfgEntry.description: Represents entry for Snooping switch Configuration.

agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol.name: agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol
agentSwitchSnoopingProtocol.description: The protocol type of network protocol in use.

agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingAdminMode.description: This enables or disables Snooping on the system.

agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.name: agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask
agentSwitchSnoopingPortMask.description: IGMP/MLD Snooping Port Mask. This allows configuration of IGMP/MLD Snooping on selected ports. IGMP/MLD Snooping cannot be enabled on an interface that has routing enabled, or is a member of a LAG. If a port which has IGMP/MLD Snooping enabled becomes enabled for routing, or is enlisted as a member of a LAG, IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be disabled on that port. IGMP/MLD Snooping functionality will be subsequently be reenabled if routing is disabled or LAG membership is removed from an interface that had previously had IGMP/MLD Snooping enabled. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFrame.name: agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFramesProcessed
agentSwitchSnoopingMulticastControlFrame.description: Multicast Control Frames Processed by CPU. The number of multicast control frames that have been processed by the CPU.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfTable
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Interface configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfEntry.description: Represents entry for a IGMP/MLD Snooping Interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfIndex.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfIndex
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfIndex.description: The port number to be selected. Each port maps to an interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on a selected interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfGroupMembershipIn.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfGroupMembershipInterval
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfGroupMembershipIn.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a report from a particular group on the selected interface before deleting the interface from the entry. This value must be greater than agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMaxResponseTime.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMRPExpirationTime.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMRPExpirationTime
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMRPExpirationTime.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a query to be received on the selected interface before the interface is removed from the list of interfaces with multicast routers attached.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfFastLeaveAdminMod.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfFastLeaveAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfFastLeaveAdminMod.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on the selected interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMulticastRouterMo.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMulticastRouterMode
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMulticastRouterMo.description: This enables or disables Multicast Routing on the selected interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingIntfVlanIDs.name: agentSwitchSnoopingIntfVlanIDs
agentSwitchSnoopingIntfVlanIDs.description: This field lists all the VlanIDs which include the selected interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Snooping Vlan configuration entries.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanEntry.description: Represents entry for a IGMP/MLD Snooping Vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on a selected Vlan interface.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipIn.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipInterval
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanGroupMembershipIn.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a report from a particular group on the selected vlan before deleting the interface participating in the vlan from the entry. This value must be greater than agentSwitchSnoopingIntfMaxResponseTime.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMaxResponseTime.description: The amount of time in seconds a switch will wait after sending a query on the selected vlan because it did not receive a report for a particular group in the interface participating in the vlan. This value must be less than agentSwitchSnoopingIntfGroupMembershipInterval. For IGMP Snooping, this value ranges from 1 to 25 and for MLD Snooping, this value ranges from 1 to 65.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMod.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMode
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanFastLeaveAdminMod.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Snooping on the selected vlan.

agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime.name: agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime
agentSwitchSnoopingVlanMRPExpirationTime.description: The amount of time in seconds that a switch will wait for a query to be received on the selected interface participating in the vlan before the interface is removed from the list of interfaces with multicast routers attached. This parameter is configurable only for exisiting Vlans.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterTable.description: A table of the IGMP/MLD Static Mrouter Configuration parameters.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterEntry.description: Represents entry for a IGMP/MLD Static Mrouter.

agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode.name: agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode
agentSwitchVlanStaticMrouterAdminMode.description: This enables or disables IGMP/MLD Mrouter on a per-interface per-vlan basis.

agentSwitchMFDBEntry.name: agentSwitchMFDBEntry
agentSwitchMFDBEntry.description: Contains Forwarding and Filtering information per Vlan Index, MAC Address, and Component User.

agentSwitchMFDBVlanId.name: agentSwitchMFDBVlanId
agentSwitchMFDBVlanId.description: Vlan Index for which this entry is associated with.

agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress.name: agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress
agentSwitchMFDBMacAddress.description: A multicast MAC address for which the switch has forwarding and or filtering information.

agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType.name: agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType
agentSwitchMFDBProtocolType.description: The component that is responsible for this entry in the Multicast Forwarding Database.

agentSwitchMFDBType.name: agentSwitchMFDBType
agentSwitchMFDBType.description: This displays the type of the entry. static(1) - Entries configured by the end user dynamic(2) - Entries added as a result of a learning process or protocol if agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask is all zero means there is no such agentSwitchMFDBType assigned forwarding port.

agentSwitchMFDBDescription.name: agentSwitchMFDBDescription
agentSwitchMFDBDescription.description: Text description of this multicast table entry.

agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBForwardingPortMask.description: BitMask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be forwarded. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBFilteringPortMask.description: BitMask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be filtered. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryTable.description: The Multicast Forwarding Database Summary table

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryEntry.description: Summarizes the forwarding ports for all components registered for all MFDB table entries with the same Vlan Index and MAC Address.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryVlanId.description: Vlan Index for which this entry is associated with.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryMacAddress.description: A multicast MAC address for which the switch has forwarding and or filtering information.

agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask.name: agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask
agentSwitchMFDBSummaryForwardingPortMask.description: Port Mask indicating which ports this entry indicates should be forwarded. To obtain port numbers from interface numbers, use the objects agentPortDot1dBasePort and agentPortIfIndex in the agentPortConfigTable table.

agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries.name: agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries
agentSwitchMFDBMaxTableEntries.description: This displays the maximum number of entries that can possibly be in the Multicast Forwarding Database table.

agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed.name: agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed
agentSwitchMFDBMostEntriesUsed.description: This displays the largest number of entries that have been present in the Multicast Forwarding Database table. This value is also known as the MFDB high-water mark.

agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries.name: agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries
agentSwitchMFDBCurrentEntries.description: This displays the current number of entries in the Multicast Forwarding Database table.

agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype
agentSwitchDVlanTagEthertype.description: Configures the Double Vlan Tag Ethertype for the switch. If this object is supported, ethertype cannot be configured per port. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

agentSwitchDVlanTagTable.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagTable
agentSwitchDVlanTagTable.description: A table of entries specifying the ethertype (TPID) values. This will let the user specify multiple ethertypes globally.

agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry
agentSwitchDVlanTagEntry.description: A table entry specifying the ethertype (TPID) values. Commonly used are the Ethertypes for vman tags (34984, or 0x88A8) and dot1q tags (33024, or 0x8100).

agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid
agentSwitchDVlanTagTPid.description: Ethertype value to identify incoming double tagged frames

agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid.name: agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid
agentSwitchDVlanTagPrimaryTPid.description: Specifies if this TPID is primary TPID for the switch or not

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTable.description: A table entries specifying the ethertype (TPID) values per port.

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagEntry.description: A table entry specifying the ethertype (TPID) value for a port.

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex
agentSwitchPortDVlanTagInterfaceIfIndex.description: Port Id on to which the Ethertype value is mapped

agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTPid.name: agentSwitchPortDVlanTagTPid

agentPortDefaultType.name: agentPortDefaultType
agentPortDefaultType.description: This object identifies the default administrative port type, to be used in conjunction with the operational port type denoted by agentPortType. The set of possible values for this object is the same as the set defined for the agentPortType object. This object represents the administratively-configured type of the MAU. If auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, the value of this object determines the operational type of the MAU. In this case, a set to this object will force the MAU into the specified operating mode. If auto-negotiation is implemented and enabled for this MAU, the operational type of the MAU is determined by auto-negotiation, and the value of this object denotes the type to which the MAU will automatically revert if/when auto-negotiation is later disabled. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType1000BaseSXFD dot3MauType10GBaseLW dot3MauType1000BaseXFD dot3MauType10GigBaseX

agentPortType.name: agentPortType
agentPortType.description: This object identifies the port type. An initial set of MAU types are defined in RFC 2668. The assignment of OBJECT IDENTIFIERs to new types of MAUs is managed by the IANA. If the MAU type is unknown, the object identifier unknownMauType OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is returned. Note that unknownMauType is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and the BER must be able to generate and recognize this value. This object represents the operational type of the MAU, as determined by either (1) the result of the auto-negotiation function or (2) if auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for this MAU, by the value of the object agentPortDefaultType, or (3) for the GigE card a value determined by the GBIC connected to the card. In case (2), a set to the object agentPortDefaultType will force the MAU into the new operating mode. The valid values for this object are: dot3MauType10BaseTHD dot3MauType10BaseTFD dot3MauType100BaseTXHD dot3MauType100BaseTXFD dot3MauType100BaseFXFD dot3MauType1000BaseSXFD dot3MauType1000BaseTFD dot3MauType10GBaseLW dot3MauType1000BaseXFD dot3MauType10GigBaseX

agentStpCstHelloTime.description: The MSTP root port hello time for the CIST.

agentStpCstMaxAge.description: The MSTP root port max age for the CIST.

agentStpCstRegionalRootId.description: The MSTP regional root identifier for the CIST.

agentStpCstRegionalRootPathCost.description: The MSTP regional root path cost for the CIST.

agentStpCstBridgeFwdDelay.description: The MSTP bridge forward delay for the CIST. The default value is 15.

agentStpCstBridgeHelloTime.description: The MSTP bridge hello time for the CIST. The default value is 2. According to IEEE 802.1Q-REV 2005 updating hello time is disallowed

agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.name: agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime
agentStpCstBridgeHoldTime.description: The MSTP bridge hold time for the CIST.

agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.name: agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge
agentStpCstBridgeMaxAge.description: The MSTP bridge max age for the CIST. The default value is 20.

agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.name: agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops
agentStpCstBridgeMaxHops.description: The MSTP bridge max hops for the CIST. The default value is 20.

agentStpCstBridgePriority.name: agentStpCstBridgePriority
agentStpCstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority for the CIST. The default value is 32768.

agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.name: agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount
agentStpCstBridgeHoldCount.description: The MSTP bridge hold count for the CIST. This command sets the value of maximum bpdus that a bridge is allowed to send within a hello time window. The default value is 6.

agentStpCstPortOperEdge.name: agentStpCstPortOperEdge
agentStpCstPortOperEdge.description: The MSTP operational status of a specific port for the CIST.

agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.name: agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint
agentStpCstPortOperPointToPoint.description: The MSTP operational point to point mac of a specific port for the CIST.

agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.name: agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck
agentStpCstPortTopologyChangeAck.description: The MSTP topology change acknowledge for a specific port in the CIST.

agentStpCstPortEdge.name: agentStpCstPortEdge
agentStpCstPortEdge.description: The administrative state of a specific port in CIST. enable(1) - enables the port. disable(2) - disables the port. The default port state is disabled.

agentStpCstPortForwardingState.name: agentStpCstPortForwardingState
agentStpCstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstPortId.name: agentStpCstPortId
agentStpCstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstPortPathCost.name: agentStpCstPortPathCost
agentStpCstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in CIST. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

agentStpCstPortPriority.name: agentStpCstPortPriority
agentStpCstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in CIST. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.name: agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId
agentStpCstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstDesignatedCost.name: agentStpCstDesignatedCost
agentStpCstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstDesignatedPortId.name: agentStpCstDesignatedPortId
agentStpCstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in CIST.

agentStpCstExtPortPathCost.name: agentStpCstExtPortPathCost
agentStpCstExtPortPathCost.description: The MSTP external port path cost in CIST. The default value varies depending upon the link speed.

agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.name: agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect
agentStpCstPortBpduGuardEffect.description: BPDU Guard Mode effect on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Guard Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Guard Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortBpduFilter.name: agentStpCstPortBpduFilter
agentStpCstPortBpduFilter.description: This command sets BPDU Filter mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Filter Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Filter Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortBpduFlood.name: agentStpCstPortBpduFlood
agentStpCstPortBpduFlood.description: This command sets BPDU Flood mode on the port. enable(1) - BPDU Flood Mode is enabled on the port. disable(2) - BPDU Flood Mode is disabled on the port.

agentStpCstPortAutoEdge.name: agentStpCstPortAutoEdge
agentStpCstPortAutoEdge.description: This command sets the auto-edge mode of the port which enables it to become an edge port if it does not see BPDUs for some duration. enable(1) - enables the auto-edge mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the auto-edge mode for the port. The default auto-edge mode is enabled.

agentStpCstPortRootGuard.name: agentStpCstPortRootGuard
agentStpCstPortRootGuard.description: This command sets a port to discard any superior information received by the port and thus protect against root of the device from changing.The port gets put into discarding state and does not forward any packets. enable(1) - enables the root-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the root-guard mode for the port. The default root-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpCstPortTCNGuard.name: agentStpCstPortTCNGuard
agentStpCstPortTCNGuard.description: This command restricts the port from propagating any topology change information received through that port. enable(1) - enables the tcn-guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the tcn-guard mode for the port. The default tcn-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpCstPortLoopGuard.name: agentStpCstPortLoopGuard
agentStpCstPortLoopGuard.description: This command enables loop guard on this port. This setting applies to all Spanning Tree instances of which this port is a member. enable(1) - enables the loop guard mode for the port. disable(2) - disables the loop guard mode for the port. The default loop-guard mode is disabled.

agentStpMstBridgePriority.name: agentStpMstBridgePriority
agentStpMstBridgePriority.description: The MSTP bridge priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 4096. The recommended default value is 32768.

agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.name: agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier
agentStpMstBridgeIdentifier.description: The MSTP bridge identifier in a specific instance.

agentStpMstDesignatedRootId.name: agentStpMstDesignatedRootId
agentStpMstDesignatedRootId.description: The MSTP designated root bridge identifier in a specific instance.

agentStpMstRootPathCost.name: agentStpMstRootPathCost
agentStpMstRootPathCost.description: The MSTP root path cost in a specific instance.

agentStpMstRootPortId.name: agentStpMstRootPortId
agentStpMstRootPortId.description: The MSTP root port ID in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange
agentStpMstTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The MSTP time since the last topology change in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.name: agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount
agentStpMstTopologyChangeCount.description: The MSTP count of topology changes in a specific instance.

agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.name: agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm
agentStpMstTopologyChangeParm.description: The MSTP topology change parameter in a specific instance.

agentStpMstRowStatus.name: agentStpMstRowStatus
agentStpMstRowStatus.description: The MSTP instance status. Supported values: active(1) - valid instance. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new instance. destroy(6) - removes an instance.

agentStpMstPortForwardingState.name: agentStpMstPortForwardingState
agentStpMstPortForwardingState.description: The MSTP forwarding state of a specific port in a specific instance.

agentStpMstPortId.name: agentStpMstPortId
agentStpMstPortId.description: The MSTP port identifier of a specific port in a specific instance.

agentStpMstPortPathCost.name: agentStpMstPortPathCost
agentStpMstPortPathCost.description: The MSTP port path cost in a specific instance. The default value will correspond to the recommendation specified in IEEE 802.1s Table 13-2 which varies depending upon link speed.

agentStpMstPortPriority.name: agentStpMstPortPriority
agentStpMstPortPriority.description: The MSTP port priority in a specific instance. The priority is in the increments of 16. The default value is 128.

agentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.name: agentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId
agentStpMstDesignatedBridgeId.description: The MSTP designated bridge ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

agentStpMstDesignatedCost.name: agentStpMstDesignatedCost
agentStpMstDesignatedCost.description: The MSTP designated cost of a specific port in a specific instance.

agentStpMstDesignatedPortId.name: agentStpMstDesignatedPortId
agentStpMstDesignatedPortId.description: The MSTP designated port ID of a specific port in a specific instance.

agentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.name: agentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState
agentStpMstPortLoopInconsistentState.description: The loop inconsistent state of a specific port in a specific instance. This value can only report as true(1) when loop guard is enabled on the port and the port has transitioned from blocking state in this MST instance.

agentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopIncons.name: agentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopInconsistentState
agentStpMstPortTransitionsIntoLoopIncons.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned into loop inconsistent state.

agentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopIncon.name: agentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopInconsistentState
agentStpMstPortTransitionsOutOfLoopIncon.description: The number of times this interface has transitioned out of loop inconsistent state.

agentStpMstVlanRowStatus.name: agentStpMstVlanRowStatus
agentStpMstVlanRowStatus.description: The association status of an MSTP instance and a VLAN. Supported values: active(1) - valid association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN. destroy(6) - removes the association between an MSTP instance and a VLAN.

agentStpBpduGuardMode.name: agentStpBpduGuardMode
agentStpBpduGuardMode.description: The spanning tree BPDU Guard Mode. enable(1) - enables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Guard Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

agentStpBpduFilterDefault.name: agentStpBpduFilterDefault
agentStpBpduFilterDefault.description: The spanning tree BPDU Filter Mode, it enables BPDU Filter on all edge ports. enable(1) - enables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. disable(2) - disables BPDU Filter Mode on the switch. The default status is disabled.

agentAuthenticationListCreate.name: agentAuthenticationListCreate
agentAuthenticationListCreate.description: Authentication List Create If set to a non empty string, creates a new Authentication Login List for configuration.

agentAuthenticationEnableListCreate.name: agentAuthenticationEnableListCreate
agentAuthenticationEnableListCreate.description: Authentication Enable List Create If set to a non empty string, creates a new Authentication Enable List for configuration.

agentAuthenticationListIndex.name: agentAuthenticationListIndex
agentAuthenticationListIndex.description: Authenticaiton List Index Unique number used for indexing into this table.

agentAuthenticationListName.name: agentAuthenticationListName
agentAuthenticationListName.description: Authenticaiton List Name Unique name used to identify the Authentication List from other tables.

agentAuthenticationListMethod1.name: agentAuthenticationListMethod1
agentAuthenticationListMethod1.description: Authenticion List Method 1 Configures the first authentication method to use when this list is specified.

agentAuthenticationListMethod2.name: agentAuthenticationListMethod2
agentAuthenticationListMethod2.description: Authenticion List Method 2 Configures the second authentication method to use when this list is specified.

agentAuthenticationListMethod3.name: agentAuthenticationListMethod3
agentAuthenticationListMethod3.description: Authenticion List Method 3 Configures the third authentication method to use when this list is specified.

agentAuthenticationListStatus.description: The status of the Authentication List. Supported values: active(1) - indicates a valid Authenticaiton List destroy(6) - removes the Authentication List.

agentAuthenticationListMethod4.name: agentAuthenticationListMethod4
agentAuthenticationListMethod4.description: Authenticion List Method 4 Configures the fourth authentication method to use when this list is specified.

agentAuthenticationListMethod6.name: agentAuthenticationListMethod6
agentAuthenticationListMethod6.description: Authenticion List Method 6 Configures the sixth authentication method to use when this list is specified.

agentAuthenticationListAccessType.description: Authenticion List Access Type Shows the authentication list access type. cts is the authentication list type for console, telnet, and ssh.

agentAuthenticationListAccessLevel.name: agentAuthenticationListAccessLevel
agentAuthenticationListAccessLevel.description: Authenticion List Access Level Shows the authentication list access level.

agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationList.name: agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationList
agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationList.description: Default Authentication List This object configures which authentication list to use for users which do not have an Authentication List configured. The list must be configured before setting.

agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationDot1.name: agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationDot1xList
agentUserConfigDefaultAuthenticationDot1.description: Default Authentication List 802.1x This object configures which authentication list to use for users which do not have an Authentication List configured. The list must be configured before setting.

agentUserAuthenticationList.name: agentUserAuthenticationList
agentUserAuthenticationList.description: User Authentication List This object configures which authentication list to use for this user. The list must be configured before setting.

agentUserAuthenticationDot1xList.name: agentUserAuthenticationDot1xList
agentUserAuthenticationDot1xList.description: User Authentication List 802.1x This object configures which authentication list to use for this user. The list must be configured before setting.

agentUserPortSecurity.name: agentUserPortSecurity
agentUserPortSecurity.description: User Port Port Security This object configures which ports the user has access to. Ports are indexed based on dot1dBasePort entries in dot1dBasePortTable.

agentClassOfServicePortTable.name: agentClassOfServicePortTable
agentClassOfServicePortTable.description: A table that contains information about the 802.1p priority mapping to traffic class priority queue for every physical port.

agentClassOfServicePortEntry.name: agentClassOfServicePortEntry
agentClassOfServicePortEntry.description: A 802.1p priority mapped to a traffic class priority queue.

agentClassOfServicePortPriority.name: agentClassOfServicePortPriority
agentClassOfServicePortPriority.description: The Priority value determined for the received frame. This value is equivalent to the priority indicated in the tagged frame received, or one of the evaluated priorities, determined according to the media-type. For untagged frames received from Ethernet media, this value is equal to the dot1dPortDefaultUserPriority value for the ingress port.

agentClassOfServicePortClass.name: agentClassOfServicePortClass
agentClassOfServicePortClass.description: Traffic class priority queue the received frame is mapped to.

agentHTTPMaxSessions.name: agentHTTPMaxSessions
agentHTTPMaxSessions.description: Configures the maximum number of allowable HTTP sessions. The default value is 16.

agentHTTPHardTimeout.name: agentHTTPHardTimeout
agentHTTPHardTimeout.description: Configures the hard timeout for HTTP sessions in hours. The default value is 24 hours. A value of zero means http will not timeout.

agentHTTPSoftTimeout.name: agentHTTPSoftTimeout
agentHTTPSoftTimeout.description: Configures the soft (activity) timeout for HTTP sessions in minutes. The default value is 5 minutes. A value of zero means http will not timeout.

agentAutoinstallAutosaveMode.name: agentAutoinstallAutosaveMode
agentAutoinstallAutosaveMode.description: Enable/Disable Auto Save of downloaded configuration on device.

agentAutoinstallUnicastRetryCount.name: agentAutoinstallUnicastRetryCount
agentAutoinstallUnicastRetryCount.description: Sets number of unicast TFTP attempts for configuration file.

agentAutoinstallStatus.name: agentAutoinstallStatus
agentAutoinstallStatus.description: Display current Autoinstall status on device.

agentAutoinstallAutoRebootMode.name: agentAutoinstallAutoRebootMode
agentAutoinstallAutoRebootMode.description: Enable/Disable Auto Reboot after succesfull image update on device.

agentAutoinstallOperationalMode.name: agentAutoinstallOperationalMode
agentAutoinstallOperationalMode.description: Enable/Disable Autoinstall operational mode on device.

agentAutoinstallAutoUpgradeMode.name: agentAutoinstallAutoUpgradeMode
agentAutoinstallAutoUpgradeMode.description: Enable/Disable Autoinstall auto upgrade mode on device.

agentDDnsConfigTable.name: agentDDnsConfigTable
agentDDnsConfigTable.description: A table of the switch's DDNS Config entries

agentDDnsIndex.name: agentDDnsIndex
agentDDnsIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the entry in the table.

agentDDnsServName.name: agentDDnsServName
agentDDnsServName.description: The DDNS server name of the DDNS service provider.

agentDDnsUserName.name: agentDDnsUserName
agentDDnsUserName.description: The user name of DDNS account. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters.

agentDDnsPassword.name: agentDDnsPassword
agentDDnsPassword.description: The password of DDNS account. It can be up to 32 alphanumeric characters.

agentDDnsHost.name: agentDDnsHost
agentDDnsHost.description: The host name of DDNS client. It can be up to 40 alphanumeric characters.

agentDDnsStatus.name: agentDDnsStatus
agentDDnsStatus.description: Agent DDNS Status. active(1) - This DDNS setting is active. createAndGo(4) - used to create a new entry. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this DDNS setting.

agentUdldConfigTable.name: agentUdldConfigTable
agentUdldConfigTable.description: A table of the switch's SNTP dynamic server entries

agentSaveConfig.name: agentSaveConfig
agentSaveConfig.description: enable(1) will initiate an configuration save to nvram. Status is returned by the object agentSaveConfigStatus.

agentResetSystem.name: agentResetSystem
agentResetSystem.description: Resets the switch. This object is not valid for stacking platforms.

agentConfigCurrentSystemTime.name: agentConfigCurrentSystemTime
agentConfigCurrentSystemTime.description: Current System Time in hh:mm:ss D M Y format, e.g., 13:45:50 25 9 2004. Users have to disable agentSntpClientMode in SNTP-CLIENT-MIB before configuring agentConfigCurrentSystemTime.

agentCpuLoadOneMin.name: agentCpuLoadOneMin
agentCpuLoadOneMin.description: The CPU load average in 1 minute.

agentCpuLoadFiveMin.name: agentCpuLoadFiveMin
agentCpuLoadFiveMin.description: The CPU load average in 5 minutes.

agentStartupConfigErase.name: agentStartupConfigErase
agentStartupConfigErase.description: Erase the text-based configuration file stored in non-volatile memory.On read returns 0.

agentDaiSrcMacValidate.name: agentDaiSrcMacValidate
agentDaiSrcMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Sender MAC validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiDstMacValidate.name: agentDaiDstMacValidate
agentDaiDstMacValidate.description: This object indicates whether Target MAC validation in the ARP Response packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiIPValidate.name: agentDaiIPValidate
agentDaiIPValidate.description: This object indicates whether IP address validation in the ARP packets is enabled. If this object is set to 'true', validation is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', validation is disabled.

agentDaiVlanConfigTable.name: agentDaiVlanConfigTable
agentDaiVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

agentDaiVlanConfigEntry.name: agentDaiVlanConfigEntry
agentDaiVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each existing VLAN.

agentDaiVlanIndex.name: agentDaiVlanIndex
agentDaiVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection feature is configured.

agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.name: agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable
agentDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.description: This object indicates whether Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection is disabled.

agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.name: agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable
agentDaiVlanLoggingEnable.description: This object indicates whether the Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled on this VlAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection logging is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection loging is disabled.

agentDaiVlanArpAclName.name: agentDaiVlanArpAclName
agentDaiVlanArpAclName.description: This object indicates the ARP ACL name set for this VLAN.

agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.name: agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag
agentDaiVlanArpAclStaticFlag.description: This object indicates whether the ARP ACL set for this VLAN has static flag set. If this object is set to 'true', static flag is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', static flag is disabled.

agentDaiStatsReset.name: agentDaiStatsReset
agentDaiStatsReset.description: Clear the DAI statistics on all vlans. A value of reset(1) is used to reset the statistics. A read on this object will always return the value none(0). The value none(0) cannot be forcibly set by the administrator.

agentDaiVlanStatsTable.name: agentDaiVlanStatsTable
agentDaiVlanStatsTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

agentDaiVlanStatsEntry.name: agentDaiVlanStatsEntry
agentDaiVlanStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains the Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics per VLAN.

agentDaiVlanStatsIndex.name: agentDaiVlanStatsIndex
agentDaiVlanStatsIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics are retrieved.

agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.name: agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded
agentDaiVlanPktsForwarded.description: Number of valid ARP packets forwarded by DAI.

agentDaiVlanPktsDropped.name: agentDaiVlanPktsDropped
agentDaiVlanPktsDropped.description: Number of invalid ARP packets dropped by DAI.

agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.name: agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops
agentDaiVlanDhcpDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.name: agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits
agentDaiVlanDhcpPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were forwarded by DAI as there is a matching DHCP Snooping binding entry found.

agentDaiVlanAclDrops.name: agentDaiVlanAclDrops
agentDaiVlanAclDrops.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as there is no matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan and the static flag is set on this vlan.

agentDaiVlanAclPermits.name: agentDaiVlanAclPermits
agentDaiVlanAclPermits.description: Number of ARP packets that were permitted by DAI as there is a matching ARP ACL rule found for this Vlan.

agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.name: agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures
agentDaiVlanSrcMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender mac address in ARP packet didn't match the source mac in ethernet header.

agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.name: agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures
agentDaiVlanDstMacFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the target mac address in ARP reply packet didn't match the destination mac in ethernet header.

agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.name: agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures
agentDaiVlanIpValidFailures.description: Number of ARP packets that were dropped by DAI as the sender IP address in ARP packet or target IP address in ARP reply packet is invalid. Invalid addresses include 0.0.0.0, 255.255.255.255, IP multicast addresses, class E addresses (240.0.0.0/4), loopback addresses (127.0.0.0/8).

agentDaiIfConfigTable.name: agentDaiIfConfigTable
agentDaiIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDaiIfConfigEntry.name: agentDaiIfConfigEntry
agentDaiIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each physical interface capable of this feature.

agentDaiIfTrustEnable.name: agentDaiIfTrustEnable
agentDaiIfTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If this object is set to 'true', the interface is trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be forwarded without checking. If this object is set to 'false', the interface is not trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be subjected to ARP inspection.

agentDaiIfRateLimit.name: agentDaiIfRateLimit
agentDaiIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If the incoming rate of ARP packets exceeds the value of this object for consecutively burst interval seconds, ARP packets will be dropped. Value of -1 indicates that there is no rate limit.

agentDaiIfBurstInterval.name: agentDaiIfBurstInterval
agentDaiIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the burst interval value for rate limiting purpose on this interface.

agentArpAclTable.name: agentArpAclTable
agentArpAclTable.description: A table of the ARP ACL entries

agentArpAclEntry.name: agentArpAclEntry
agentArpAclEntry.description: Represents entry for an ARP ACL

agentArpAclName.name: agentArpAclName
agentArpAclName.description: Name of the ARP ACL, which must consist of 1 to 31 alphanumeric characters and uniquely identify this ARP ACL. This object must be set to complete a new ARP ACL row instance.
